<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
An inorganic material used as a <a title="white pigment" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/white_pigment">white pigment</a> in printing inks. Lithopone is composed of barium sulfate (60:72%) and zinc sulfide (28:40%) (chemical formulae BaSO4 and ZnS, respectively). It is an opaque pigment used as an <a title="Extender" href="Extender">extender</a> in many inks. It is chemically inert, but is susceptible to decomposition when in contact with acids. (See <a title="White Pigments" href="White_Pigments">White Pigments</a>.) 
</p>
<p id="l3">
('CI Pigment White 5 No. 77115'.) 
</p>
